  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Programme title:&#xC2;&#xA0;Forecast Based Financing and Preparedness&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0;
Objective: The most vulnerable populations at risk of disaster receive well targeted and timely local action through improved National Society capacity on early action and preparedness, and better use of risk-informed analysis.
&#xC2;&#xA0;
A.&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;Work with National Societies (NS) to support their development of EAPs and strengthen the required systems and capacities to enable access to anticipatory funding: &#xC2;&#xA3;400,000 per year (&#xC2;&#xA3;100-200,000 per NS/year depending on NS capacity and status of EAP development)
B. Regional Capacity and Scale up for Early Action and Forecast Based Financing (FbF) and Preparedness for Effective Response (PER): &#xC2;&#xA3;100,000 per year&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0;
Total proposal value per year: &#xC2;&#xA3;500,000
Total proposal value April 2020&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; March 2024: &#xC2;&#xA3;2 million
Note: this proposal is in addition to an already agreed &#xC2;&#xA3;1.5m per year contribution to be used by IFRC flexibly across the DREF and FbA in order to enable NS to be eligible to access these funds.
&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;</narrative>
  </description>
